title.rendered: BSN medical Fixomull Stretch Tape, Sizes 5cm x 10m

content.rendered:
Fixomull Stretch is permeable to moisture and air, reducing the risk of maceration. It is also radiotransparent, so it does not need to be removed for either radiotherapy or X-ray examinations.  Fixomull Stretch can be cut to the required size, which means it can be tailored to protect the entire wound dressing against contamination.  It also eliminates unnecessary wastage.
Fixomull Stretch is a wide area adhesive tape, especially suitable for use on frequently mobile and highly contoured parts of the body. It is made from a white, stretchable, non-woven polyester dressing sheet coated with skin-friendly polyacrylate adhesive on the quick-release backing paper. The adhesive ensures the dressing is firmly secured on all sides and cannot slip or become detached.
